    "# CS672 – Project 2: Deep Learning Models for NYC Taxi Trip Duration Prediction\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objective\n",
    "Build and compare three **TensorFlow regression models** to predict NYC Yellow Taxi trip duration using:\n",
    "- cleaned taxi trip data from Project 1\n",
    "- NYC daily weather data from Meteostat\n",
    "\n",
    "### Required TensorFlow models\n",
    "1. **Linear Regression** (Sequential model with no hidden layers)\n",
    "2. **MLP** (Multi-Layer Perceptron)\n",
    "3. **DNN** (at least 2 hidden layers)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Required evaluation setup\n",
    "- **80/20 time-sensitive split**\n",
    "- **Loss functions:** MSE and MAE\n",
    "- **Optimizers:** SGD, Adam, RMSProp\n",
    "- **Epochs:** 100\n",
    "- **Batch size:** 32\n",
    "- Plot **training loss vs validation loss**\n",
    "- Select the **best TensorFlow model**\n",
    "- Use `model.predict()` for final predictions\n",
    "\n",
    "### Extra Credit\n",
    "Build a **PyTorch DNN** and compare it against the TensorFlow DNN."
   ]
  },
